begin_memory_text: We talked about how he bought a house during Covid when his landlord told him he had 60 days to be out of the place he was renting.
middle_memory_text: We talked about his work as a programmer and how he got into doing that and about my current and previous work.
end_memory_text: We talked about repairs and work he's been doing around the house since he bought it and a little about gardening and growing tomatoes and strawberries.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of the week will be stressful and exhausting. I'm headed to an out of town appointment tomorrow, working and running errands Wednesday, and getting new tires on the car Thursday. Normally, my schedule is not so busy. Plus, my husband hasn't been feeling well and hasn't been helping much around the house and I feel like that leaves more on me.
critical_positive: I think we both wanted to be kind and make this work out for both of us. We were polite and stuck to safe topics of conversation. Since he had recently bought a house, that provided a lot of things to talk about. Since we're also trying to buy, I felt like that gave us some common ground.
critical_negative: This felt like the kind of conversation you have with someone you don't know that well. Very safe, but not a place where you talk about anything that is particularly important to you or about which you're particularly passionate. It felt kind of boring and empty. I somewhat felt he wasn't sharing a lot and I didn't want to pry.

begin_memory_text: We talked about COVID and being at home a lot.  We both discussed how it was to be home so much.
middle_memory_text: We mostly talked about our family situations, what we do for a living, our homes, and our background to our careers.
end_memory_text: We mostly talked about gardening and how tomatoes and strawberries are different when you grow them at home than when you buy them from the store.
rest_of_day_open: I expect that I will have a fairly hard work week as I have many things due this week.  I expect that I won't have a lot of time to hang around with the family because of some of my responsibilities.  I expect to be in a lot of meetings.
critical_positive: I think we both just started talking without needing a lot of prompting.  When we did come to a slight pause we were easily able to keep the discussion going with a quick question. She was very easy to talk to as she was pretty kicked back and kind.  We had a lot in common with homes.
critical_negative: The only thing that maybe didn't work as well was that we didn't have some of our "big" things in common.  My favorite things are being in the outdoors and hunting and fishing, she was more into gardening.  I have kids and she doesn't so we didn't really talk much about that aspect.
